<p>The <b>black-throated loon</b> (<i>Gavia arctica</i>) is a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird_migration" title="Bird migration">migratory</a> aquatic bird found in the northern hemisphere. The species is known as an <b>Arctic loon</b> in North America and the <b>black-throated diver</b> in Eurasia. Its current name is a compromise proposed by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/International_Ornithological_Committee" title="International Ornithological Committee">International Ornithological Committee</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="Gavia_arctica#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
